Most probably your parser couldn&#39;t match anything in the input. ANTLR parsers don&#39;t try to process the entire input unless your grammar rules force them (say if you have EOF in your rules.) Check stderr for parser messages, or try to run your input through grun to see what your parser sees. Keep in mind that if your grammar rules allow empty input then it&#39;s correct outcome, say if your start rule says something like

    file : (record)*;

then an empty parse tree is a syntactically correct result when no `record` can be matched.

